You are building a production-grade multi-agent backend system in Python.

STRICT RULES:
- Never merge agents into one file unless explicitly asked
- Every agent must be independent module
- All agents must communicate via structured JSON only
- No hardcoded logic inside coordinator except orchestration
- LLM usage only in designated agents (Advisor Agent)
- Always return clean, typed outputs (no random text)
- Prefer simple, readable architecture over complex frameworks

ARCHITECTURE RULE:
Coordinator → Data Collector → Analyzer → Advisor → Notifier

ENGINEERING RULES:
- Always separate concerns
- Always design for extensibility
- Always assume system will scale
- Add logging for every agent step
- Handle failure with retry logic (max 2 retries)

OUTPUT RULE:
- Keep responses structured
- No unnecessary explanations in code